Henderson Global Investors Ltd.,
which oversees 65.4 billion pounds ($101 billion), said it
appointed Jim  Irvine  as head of fixed-income business.  Irvine, currently head of structured products and advisory,
will take over from Mitesh Sheth on Feb. 1. Sheth will become
director of business innovation, the London-based asset manager
said today in a statement.  Colin Fleury, head of asset-backed securities, will take
over the management of the renamed secured credit business from
Irvine.  Hendersonâ€™s fixed-income business manages 16 billion
